1
00:00:09,012 --> 00:00:09,808
<i>C'mon!</i>

2
00:00:16,185 --> 00:00:18,813
<i>Running like a fugitive,</i>

3
00:00:19,856 --> 00:00:22,017
<i>Being chased by something</i>

4
00:00:23,693 --> 00:00:26,355
<i>Inside my heart is pounding</i>

5
00:00:27,463 --> 00:00:30,091
<i>My throat dry like it's withering</i>

6
00:00:31,801 --> 00:00:34,895
<i>For no single one,</i>

7
00:00:35,538 --> 00:00:38,666
<i>To none does belong,</i>

8
00:00:40,143 --> 00:00:44,512
<i>This time is ours, right now...</i>

9
00:00:47,150 --> 00:00:48,913
<i>Unraveling the pain,</i>

10
00:00:49,018 --> 00:00:50,747
<i>Unraveling our hearts,</i>

11
00:00:50,820 --> 00:00:53,152
<i>Unraveling shadows</i>

12
00:00:54,691 --> 00:00:56,454
<i>Stifling our breath,</i>

13
00:00:56,526 --> 00:00:58,426
<i>Reaching for beyond,</i>

14
00:00:58,494 --> 00:01:00,928
<i>Tearing through the dark</i>

15
00:01:02,832 --> 00:01:09,396
<i>In fighting and in love</i>

16
00:01:10,506 --> 00:01:12,997
<i>To the distant light above,</i>

17
00:01:13,776 --> 00:01:16,643
<i>Yes, we are on the way</i>

18
00:01:21,484 --> 00:01:22,781
<i>I wanna rock...</i>

19
00:01:25,254 --> 00:01:26,778
<i>Rockin' my heart</i>

20
00:01:53,960 --> 00:01:56,952
I see. Sakura, you've come, too.

21
00:01:59,566 --> 00:02:03,400
Now you can formally register
for the Chunin Exam.

22
00:02:05,472 --> 00:02:06,496
What do you mean?

23
00:02:06,973 --> 00:02:09,567
Actually, from the start,

24
00:02:09,643 --> 00:02:14,910
only three man squads could
apply and take the exams.

25
00:02:15,382 --> 00:02:18,078
But Sensei, you said that the decision
to take the exams

26
00:02:18,151 --> 00:02:19,584
was up to the individual.

27
00:02:20,253 --> 00:02:21,811
Yes... I said that.

28
00:02:22,589 --> 00:02:23,920
Were you lying?

29
00:02:25,058 --> 00:02:26,457
Yes, I was...

30
00:02:28,161 --> 00:02:29,924
If I said that,

31
00:02:30,597 --> 00:02:34,795
Sasuke and Naruto would probably
forcefully convince you to take it.

32
00:02:37,204 --> 00:02:39,434
Even if you didn't have
the will to apply,

33
00:02:39,906 --> 00:02:41,669
if Sasuke asks you

34
00:02:41,741 --> 00:02:44,972
you would attempt to take
the exams half heartedly.

35
00:02:45,812 --> 00:02:49,612
For Sasuke's sake and,
well, Naruto's.

36
00:02:49,850 --> 00:02:51,010
Then, if...

37
00:02:51,084 --> 00:02:54,520
it had only been Sasuke and
Naruto who had come here?

38
00:02:54,955 --> 00:02:56,820
I would've stopped the Exam here.

39
00:02:57,457 --> 00:02:59,925
I wouldn't have felt like letting
them go beyond this point.

40
00:03:00,927 --> 00:03:04,158
But... you guys came here
on your own will.

41
00:03:05,031 --> 00:03:05,895
Sakura!

42
00:03:07,500 --> 00:03:08,467
Naruto!

43
00:03:09,836 --> 00:03:10,996
And, Sasuke!

44
00:03:14,274 --> 00:03:15,502
I'm glad you came.

45
00:03:16,476 --> 00:03:18,876
You're a team I'm proud of.

46
00:03:19,913 --> 00:03:21,346
Now then, go on!

47
00:03:22,349 --> 00:03:24,078
Okay! Let's go!

48
00:03:48,808 --> 00:03:54,644
<i>Genin Takedown!</i>
<i>All Nine Rookies Face Off!</i>

49
00:03:55,649 --> 00:03:57,116
W-Wow!

50
00:03:59,586 --> 00:04:01,554
W-What's with... this?

51
00:04:08,194 --> 00:04:09,718
<i>There are so many of them...</i>

52
00:04:10,230 --> 00:04:12,596
<i>Could it be that they're all applicants?</i>

53
00:04:19,172 --> 00:04:22,471
<i>They...all look...immensely strong...</i>

54
00:04:25,045 --> 00:04:27,104
Sasuke, you're late!

55
00:04:29,883 --> 00:04:33,341
I thought I'd be able to see you
for the first time in awhile,

56
00:04:33,420 --> 00:04:35,888
so I was waiting in excitement.

57
00:04:38,758 --> 00:04:41,249
Get away from Sasuke!
Ino Pig!

58
00:04:41,361 --> 00:04:43,591
Oh, my. It's Sakura.

59
00:04:43,663 --> 00:04:46,598
Your Billboard Brow hasn't changed, eh...
Ugly!

60
00:04:46,666 --> 00:04:48,190
What did you say?!

61
00:04:52,072 --> 00:04:53,039
What's up with this?

62
00:04:53,106 --> 00:04:53,731
Huh?

63
00:04:53,974 --> 00:04:57,740
Are you guys going to take
this bothersome Exam, too?

64
00:04:57,877 --> 00:04:59,845
Oh, it's the idiot trio.

65
00:04:59,913 --> 00:05:01,676
Quit calling us that!

66
00:05:01,848 --> 00:05:03,873
Man, this is a freaking bother...

67
00:05:04,818 --> 00:05:05,978
Shikamaru Nara.

68
00:05:06,252 --> 00:05:09,187
Always complaining,
has no motivation.

69
00:05:09,255 --> 00:05:10,847
He's a bellyaching idiot.

70
00:05:15,662 --> 00:05:16,856
Choji Akimichi.

71
00:05:17,230 --> 00:05:18,891
He's always eating something.

72
00:05:18,965 --> 00:05:21,126
That's all he is, a fat idiot.

73
00:05:21,668 --> 00:05:25,069
Sasuke... is mine. Bleah!

74
00:05:25,505 --> 00:05:26,597
Ino Yamanaka.

75
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:30,703
She's always fighting with Sakura.
She's her rival.

76
00:05:31,177 --> 00:05:32,508
A Sasuke crazy idiot.

77
00:05:32,946 --> 00:05:35,005
Yahoo, I found you!

78
00:05:35,448 --> 00:05:38,144
My my, everybody's here.

79
00:05:38,351 --> 00:05:40,319
H-Hello...

80
00:05:41,021 --> 00:05:41,783
Oh...

81
00:05:44,190 --> 00:05:45,248
Hinata Hyuga.

82
00:05:45,759 --> 00:05:48,387
She's a weird person who turns
her eyes away whenever I look at her!

83
00:05:48,828 --> 00:05:52,059
She's a gloomy and shy girl, I guess.

84
00:05:54,901 --> 00:05:56,994
Kiba Inuzuka and Akamaru.

85
00:05:57,270 --> 00:05:58,669
They're louder than I am!

86
00:05:58,838 --> 00:06:01,602
He always brings his dog and
always has a bossy look.

87
00:06:01,674 --> 00:06:02,800
He really annoys me!

88
00:06:05,478 --> 00:06:06,740
Shino Aburame.

89
00:06:07,113 --> 00:06:11,015
As for this guy, I really don't get him!

90
00:06:11,484 --> 00:06:13,213
He's a type I'm not good with.

91
00:06:13,686 --> 00:06:15,119
What did you say?

92
00:06:15,321 --> 00:06:17,789
You guys, too?!
Man.

93
00:06:18,258 --> 00:06:20,089
Ha! I see.

94
00:06:20,260 --> 00:06:23,889
This means all nine Genin rookies
are taking the Exam, eh...!

95
00:06:24,330 --> 00:06:25,058
Now then...

96
00:06:25,131 --> 00:06:27,395
How far can we go?

97
00:06:27,467 --> 00:06:28,991
Eh... Sasuke?

98
00:06:29,302 --> 00:06:29,996
Hmph!...

99
00:06:30,070 --> 00:06:32,004
You're mighty confident. Kiba.

100
00:06:32,272 --> 00:06:34,797
We've trained a great deal, so...

101
00:06:34,908 --> 00:06:36,705
We won't lose to you guys!

102
00:06:36,776 --> 00:06:38,437
Shut up!

103
00:06:38,845 --> 00:06:42,440
I don't know about Sasuke,
but I sure won't lose to the likes of you!

104
00:06:42,615 --> 00:06:44,310
I'm sorry. Naruto...

105
00:06:45,018 --> 00:06:47,213
Kiba didn't mean it like that...

106
00:06:48,054 --> 00:06:48,952
Huh?

107
00:06:52,625 --> 00:06:55,526
<i>Akamaru, you've become</i>
<i>tasty looking...</i>

108
00:07:00,867 --> 00:07:02,129
What?

109
00:07:09,042 --> 00:07:09,804
Don't step on it.

110
00:07:09,876 --> 00:07:10,740
Huh?

111
00:07:11,778 --> 00:07:12,938
I said, don't step on it.

112
00:07:13,313 --> 00:07:15,008
You're... gonna eat that?

113
00:07:18,518 --> 00:07:19,576
Hey, you guys!

114
00:07:21,054 --> 00:07:23,386
You should be a little quieter.

115
00:07:24,357 --> 00:07:30,193
You guys are the "rookie nine"...
fresh out of the academy, right?

116
00:07:31,064 --> 00:07:34,932
Carrying on like that
with cute faces... Man.

117
00:07:35,435 --> 00:07:37,062
This isn't a field trip.

118
00:07:37,570 --> 00:07:39,834
Who're you? Acting all haughty!

119
00:07:40,106 --> 00:07:44,042
I'm Kabuto Yakushi.
Anyway, take a good look around you.

120
00:08:05,131 --> 00:08:08,623
Behind you...
They're from the Rain Village.

121
00:08:08,968 --> 00:08:10,094
They're hot tempered.

122
00:08:11,004 --> 00:08:12,767
Everyone's tense before the Exam.

123
00:08:13,540 --> 00:08:16,202
I thought I'd warn you guys
before you get your butts whipped...

124
00:08:21,181 --> 00:08:22,273
I guess it can't be helped.

125
00:08:22,448 --> 00:08:25,281
You're rookies who don't know
left from right...

126
00:08:26,319 --> 00:08:28,344
You remind me of my old self.

127
00:08:29,122 --> 00:08:31,352
You're Kabuto... right?

128
00:08:31,958 --> 00:08:32,720
Yes...

129
00:08:32,959 --> 00:08:35,120
Then, is this your second time?

130
00:08:35,595 --> 00:08:36,357
No...

131
00:08:37,263 --> 00:08:38,321
It's my seventh time.

132
00:08:38,831 --> 00:08:39,593
Huh?!

133
00:08:40,099 --> 00:08:44,399
This Exam is only held twice a year,
so it's now my fourth year.

134
00:08:44,804 --> 00:08:48,797
Then that means you know
a lot about these exams?!

135
00:08:49,175 --> 00:08:50,039
Kind of...

136
00:08:50,109 --> 00:08:52,669
No kidding.
Kabuto, you're pretty awesome, huh?

137
00:08:53,079 --> 00:08:55,047
But you haven't passed.

138
00:08:55,114 --> 00:08:57,878
Yeah, well, that is the case, yes...

139
00:08:59,185 --> 00:09:02,245
Is the Chunin Exam that high a hurdle?

140
00:09:02,755 --> 00:09:05,485
Man, this is utterly bothersome...

141
00:09:05,758 --> 00:09:10,388
Then, maybe I'll give a bit of
information to my cute juniors.

142
00:09:11,831 --> 00:09:13,560
With these Ninja Info Cards.

143
00:09:14,067 --> 00:09:15,466
Ninja Info Cards?

144
00:09:16,102 --> 00:09:17,399
To put it simply,

145
00:09:17,470 --> 00:09:21,372
they're cards that have information burned
into them and coded with Chakra.

146
00:09:24,043 --> 00:09:28,139
I spent four whole years gathering
information for this Exam.

147
00:09:29,182 --> 00:09:31,412
There are close to two hundred
of these cards.

148
00:09:32,552 --> 00:09:34,315
They are pure white to the eye...

149
00:09:35,255 --> 00:09:37,450
To open the data on these cards...

150
00:09:38,458 --> 00:09:39,618
What're you doing?

151
00:09:39,959 --> 00:09:41,824
The way it works is that
no one can see the info

152
00:09:41,894 --> 00:09:43,521
without using my Chakra...

153
00:09:44,430 --> 00:09:45,954
For example... Like this...

154
00:09:47,834 --> 00:09:50,701
Whoa, awesome!
What information is this?

155
00:09:51,337 --> 00:09:53,897
The number of test takers and
participating nations,

156
00:09:53,973 --> 00:09:56,908
and the number of applicants
from each respective village

157
00:09:56,976 --> 00:10:00,742
is individually displayed.

158
00:10:01,914 --> 00:10:03,347
Why do you think that

159
00:10:03,416 --> 00:10:05,646
the Chunin Exam is jointly
conducted in the first place?

160
00:10:12,959 --> 00:10:16,053
It's said it's done to deepen
friendship among nations first

161
00:10:16,663 --> 00:10:20,497
and to boost the Shinobi levels, second.

162
00:10:22,135 --> 00:10:23,568
"It's said"?

163
00:10:23,903 --> 00:10:24,699
That's right.

164
00:10:24,871 --> 00:10:29,501
The real aim is in the checking of
Shinobi levels of neighboring nations

165
00:10:29,575 --> 00:10:32,908
and keeping power balance equal.

166
00:10:33,579 --> 00:10:35,809
Power... Equal?

167
00:10:37,884 --> 00:10:40,512
Why such bothersome things?

168
00:10:43,589 --> 00:10:44,715
If that's not done,

169
00:10:44,791 --> 00:10:48,022
the weak nations will be invaded by
the strong nations in no time at all

170
00:10:48,094 --> 00:10:50,028
and may end up being
controlled unilaterally.

171
00:10:50,763 --> 00:10:55,757
There's a point to mutual supervision.
Probably.

172
00:10:56,402 --> 00:10:57,164
Hmph...

173
00:10:57,470 --> 00:10:58,698
Of those cards,

174
00:10:58,771 --> 00:11:01,797
are there ones with
detailed individual information?

175
00:11:02,508 --> 00:11:03,497
Yes, there are...

176
00:11:04,077 --> 00:11:05,874
Are there ones you're concerned about?

177
00:11:06,679 --> 00:11:07,646
Yes, there are!

178
00:11:08,781 --> 00:11:12,911
The information for the applicants
this time around is not perfect,

179
00:11:13,186 --> 00:11:15,051
but is burned in and saved.

180
00:11:15,521 --> 00:11:17,284
You guys included...

181
00:11:17,924 --> 00:11:21,553
About those " ones you're
concerned about," who you know.

182
00:11:21,627 --> 00:11:24,790
Anything's fine, tell me their information
and I'll retrieve it for you.

183
00:11:25,331 --> 00:11:30,064
Gaara of the Sand Village,
and Rock Lee of the Leaf Village.

184
00:11:30,303 --> 00:11:32,737
Oh, you even know names.

185
00:11:32,972 --> 00:11:34,303
That makes it quick.

186
00:11:45,418 --> 00:11:46,407
Here they are!

187
00:11:47,754 --> 00:11:48,982
Please show me.

188
00:11:57,264 --> 00:11:57,958
Here they are!

189
00:11:59,734 --> 00:12:00,894
Please show me.

190
00:12:05,973 --> 00:12:09,739
<i>I don't really get what's going on,</i>
<i>but I'll pretend like I do.</i>

191
00:12:10,344 --> 00:12:12,039
Well then, first is Rock Lee.

192
00:12:18,219 --> 00:12:21,017
He's one year older than you guys.

193
00:12:21,756 --> 00:12:25,715
His mission experience,
twenty D-ranks and eleven C-ranks.

194
00:12:26,293 --> 00:12:27,419
His squad leader is Guy...

195
00:12:27,962 --> 00:12:30,795
In just this year, his Taijutsu
has drastically improved, but...

196
00:12:30,865 --> 00:12:32,423
His other skills are not good at all.

197
00:12:34,602 --> 00:12:38,299
Last year, he'd attracted attention as
a Genin rookie with his ability,

198
00:12:39,006 --> 00:12:41,634
but didn't participate
in the Chunin Exam.

199
00:12:42,743 --> 00:12:45,974
This is his first time taking the exams,
same as you guys...

200
00:12:46,781 --> 00:12:49,944
Tenten and Neji Hyuga are on his team...

201
00:12:53,921 --> 00:12:56,151
Huh? Hyuga?

202
00:12:57,324 --> 00:12:59,792
Next... is Gaara of the Desert.

203
00:13:05,766 --> 00:13:10,260
His mission experience,
eight C ranks. B ranks...

204
00:13:10,337 --> 00:13:13,101
Wow, one B rank as a Genin, eh...

205
00:13:13,841 --> 00:13:15,775
He's a Shinobi from a different land
and is a rookie,

206
00:13:15,843 --> 00:13:17,640
so there is no further
detailed information.

207
00:13:18,979 --> 00:13:19,775
But...

208
00:13:21,482 --> 00:13:24,849
It seems he has returned from
all of his missions uninjured.

209
00:13:25,786 --> 00:13:29,620
B-rank as a Genin...
But uninjured?!

210
00:13:31,092 --> 00:13:32,525
What is this guy?

211
00:13:43,737 --> 00:13:48,470
Leaf, Sand, Rain, Grass,
Waterfall, Sound...

212
00:13:49,643 --> 00:13:52,077
There are lots of exceptional Genins
from those villages

213
00:13:52,146 --> 00:13:54,740
who have come to take
the Exam this year as well.

214
00:13:56,383 --> 00:13:59,011
As far as the Village Hidden
in Sound goes,

215
00:13:59,220 --> 00:14:02,018
it's a village of a small nation that
just sprang up in recent years,

216
00:14:02,223 --> 00:14:03,986
so there isn't much information...

217
00:14:07,761 --> 00:14:09,194
At any rate,

218
00:14:09,263 --> 00:14:11,527
they're all Hidden Villages
with nothing but crackerjacks.

219
00:14:12,066 --> 00:14:15,524
That kind of makes you lose
your confidence.

220
00:14:16,137 --> 00:14:18,230
Why are you saying that now?

221
00:14:18,506 --> 00:14:19,370
In other words...

222
00:14:19,440 --> 00:14:21,874
all of the applicants who
have gathered here...

223
00:14:22,276 --> 00:14:23,208
That's right!

224
00:14:23,344 --> 00:14:25,209
Not just Lee and Gaara,

225
00:14:25,446 --> 00:14:29,314
but they're all choice top elite
Genin from each nation.

226
00:14:29,950 --> 00:14:30,882
Hmm.

227
00:14:31,519 --> 00:14:33,885
This isn't going to be easy.

228
00:14:36,724 --> 00:14:38,419
<i>I can't go along with this!</i>

229
00:14:38,526 --> 00:14:40,892
<i>They may be your subordinates now,</i>

230
00:14:40,961 --> 00:14:43,361
<i>but they are children</i>
<i>who were my students.</i>

231
00:14:43,597 --> 00:14:44,791
<i>If it's about them I know...</i>

232
00:14:44,865 --> 00:14:47,299
<i>It's as you say, Iruka.</i>

233
00:14:49,036 --> 00:14:51,004
<i>It's not going to be that easy.</i>

234
00:14:51,305 --> 00:14:52,966
<i>You're too eager.</i>

235
00:14:53,474 --> 00:14:56,466
<i>I postponed my team's test taking</i>
<i>for one year</i>

236
00:14:56,544 --> 00:14:58,136
<i>and took care to build up</i>
<i>their skills.</i>

237
00:14:59,079 --> 00:15:01,411
<i>Have them take the Exam after</i>
<i>they've enjoyed their life a little bit more.</i>

238
00:15:02,283 --> 00:15:03,079
<i>Hmph...</i>

239
00:15:03,250 --> 00:15:05,548
<i>They might be too easygoing.</i>

240
00:15:05,619 --> 00:15:09,578
<i>But they will surpass</i>
<i>your guys in no time.</i>

241
00:15:10,958 --> 00:15:12,858
<i>That's enough.</i>

242
00:15:13,427 --> 00:15:15,725
<i>That's as far as</i>
<i>the rookie matter goes.</i>

243
00:15:16,163 --> 00:15:17,460
<i>Now then, next...</i>

244
00:15:17,665 --> 00:15:20,566
<i>I'll take recommendations for Genin</i>
<i>other than rookies.</i>

245
00:15:22,436 --> 00:15:24,700
<i>Well! Don't pour cold water on this...</i>

246
00:15:27,841 --> 00:15:29,604
<i>I said that, nevertheless...</i>

247
00:15:29,944 --> 00:15:34,540
<i>I wonder if even the fearless ones</i>
<i>are frightened just this time around.</i>

248
00:15:36,016 --> 00:15:37,711
<i>Stubborn as he is,</i>

249
00:15:37,785 --> 00:15:40,117
<i>he's still consumed by this atmosphere</i>
<i>and number of people.</i>

250
00:15:40,187 --> 00:15:41,347
<i>He's tense.</i>

251
00:15:42,223 --> 00:15:43,315
<i>It can't be helped.</i>

252
00:15:43,724 --> 00:15:49,060
<i>Even though everyone is a Genin,</i>
<i>we're the newest most inexperienced rookies.</i>

253
00:15:49,630 --> 00:15:52,394
<i>I'm very, very uneasy.</i>

254
00:15:53,067 --> 00:15:53,931
<i>But...</i>

255
00:15:54,468 --> 00:15:57,926
<i>It's kind of tough looking at</i>
<i>Naruto who's not himself.</i>

256
00:15:58,939 --> 00:16:00,770
<i>Maybe I'll cheer him up a bit.</i>

257
00:16:01,842 --> 00:16:04,834
Say... Naruto! Don't be so scared.

258
00:16:05,012 --> 00:16:05,569
Huh?

259
00:16:15,356 --> 00:16:17,722
My name's Naruto Uzumaki!

260
00:16:17,958 --> 00:16:21,758
I won't lose to any of you!
Got it?!

261
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:28,594
Say! What's with him?!

262
00:16:29,403 --> 00:16:31,803
<i>That idiot would never</i>
<i>get depressed! Absurd!</i>

263
00:16:31,939 --> 00:16:34,464
It won't do any good to
provoke everyone!

264
00:16:34,541 --> 00:16:35,633
Don't tell me!

265
00:16:35,709 --> 00:16:37,540
If I don't tell it to you,
who do I tell it to?!

266
00:16:37,611 --> 00:16:38,771
What did you say?!

267
00:16:38,846 --> 00:16:41,406
Oh, I feel better.

268
00:16:42,216 --> 00:16:43,080
Hmph...

269
00:16:50,090 --> 00:16:52,558
Isn't that the guy from before...?

270
00:16:53,027 --> 00:16:55,222
The dog's bark is
bigger than its bite.

271
00:16:56,063 --> 00:16:56,893
Is he an idiot...?

272
00:16:57,498 --> 00:16:59,159
He's mighty high-spirited.

273
00:16:59,466 --> 00:17:00,728
He's hot-headed, eh.

274
00:17:01,435 --> 00:17:04,370
Lee, maybe you did
not bully him enough.

275
00:17:09,476 --> 00:17:10,602
Did you hear?

276
00:17:10,678 --> 00:17:14,239
Sound Village is a minor
Hidden Village of a small nation.

277
00:17:14,648 --> 00:17:16,115
That's offensive.

278
00:17:16,317 --> 00:17:19,377
Maybe I'II... play with them a bit.

279
00:17:19,720 --> 00:17:24,817
Yes, being referred to as something
like leftover Shinobis and all.

280
00:17:25,492 --> 00:17:27,653
We'll add this to his data.

281
00:17:28,362 --> 00:17:32,890
Those Sound Shinobis
are brutal in their own way.

282
00:17:41,442 --> 00:17:43,967
I won't lose to any of you,
you say?

283
00:17:44,178 --> 00:17:45,543
You said it...!

284
00:17:45,879 --> 00:17:47,005
That idiot...

285
00:17:47,081 --> 00:17:50,244
In no time at all, he's made enemies
of his surroundings.

286
00:17:51,151 --> 00:17:53,016
What're you talking big for?! You!

287
00:17:53,821 --> 00:17:55,914
But, I just said what was true, I say!

288
00:18:00,661 --> 00:18:02,686
E-Everyone, that was a joke.

289
00:18:02,763 --> 00:18:04,958
This guy's quite an idiot, you see...

290
00:18:05,165 --> 00:18:07,861
After all, he says idiotic, spazzy,
scatterbrained things

291
00:18:07,935 --> 00:18:09,630
and gets carried away,

292
00:18:09,703 --> 00:18:12,035
so please don't concern
yourself with him.

293
00:18:12,239 --> 00:18:14,707
Jeez, thanks to you, I got glared at!

294
00:18:14,908 --> 00:18:16,341
I'm going to kick your butt!

295
00:18:17,778 --> 00:18:18,904
Shall we do it?

296
00:18:19,046 --> 00:18:20,274
Let's do it.

297
00:18:41,602 --> 00:18:45,766
Learn how to read atmosphere
already, you!

298
00:18:46,306 --> 00:18:47,068
Fine!

299
00:18:59,620 --> 00:19:01,645
<i>These guys...are the Sound Village...</i>

300
00:19:06,393 --> 00:19:07,485
He dodged it!

301
00:19:08,095 --> 00:19:09,687
<i>I can see through that speed.</i>

302
00:19:23,043 --> 00:19:26,012
I see... It's that kind of attack, eh?

303
00:19:28,949 --> 00:19:30,007
What's going on?

304
00:19:30,083 --> 00:19:31,345
He was supposed to have evaded it.

305
00:19:31,485 --> 00:19:32,850
Why'd that happen to his glasses?

306
00:19:33,220 --> 00:19:35,245
Probably grazed the tip of his nose.

307
00:19:35,422 --> 00:19:38,914
He's trying to act strong, so. That punk.

308
00:19:41,862 --> 00:19:42,726
Huh?!

309
00:19:50,771 --> 00:19:52,033
Oh! He puked?!

310
00:19:52,439 --> 00:19:53,736
K-Kabuto?

311
00:19:54,107 --> 00:19:54,971
Huh?!

312
00:20:04,184 --> 00:20:04,878
Hah!

313
00:20:08,055 --> 00:20:09,579
Hey, Kabuto!

314
00:20:09,656 --> 00:20:10,623
Are you okay?!

315
00:20:11,024 --> 00:20:12,582
Yeah... I'm okay.

316
00:20:12,993 --> 00:20:13,891
Really?

317
00:20:14,094 --> 00:20:17,359
Oh, so he's not so special.

318
00:20:17,664 --> 00:20:20,360
Even though he's a veteran who's
been taking the exams for four whole years.

319
00:20:20,834 --> 00:20:22,961
Write this on your card.

320
00:20:23,670 --> 00:20:26,798
The three from Sound village...
Doubtless Chunin.

321
00:20:30,811 --> 00:20:33,041
<i>Kabuto should've totally read the attack...</i>

322
00:20:34,114 --> 00:20:35,843
<i>But why did he vomit?</i>

323
00:20:41,288 --> 00:20:43,518
Lee. How about that technique just now?

324
00:20:44,157 --> 00:20:45,886
I had no problem reading the speed.

325
00:20:46,627 --> 00:20:47,889
There's some kind of trick...

326
00:20:50,664 --> 00:20:54,065
Silence! Degenerates!

327
00:21:08,682 --> 00:21:09,876
Sorry to keep you waiting... I

328
00:21:09,950 --> 00:21:16,480
I'm Ibiki Morino, proctor for the
first test of the Chunin Exam.

329
00:22:52,554 --> 00:22:56,547
It feels like the chance to show off
the fruits of our training has finally come.

330
00:22:56,625 --> 00:22:58,024
Well, no matter what kind
of test it is,

331
00:22:58,093 --> 00:22:59,822
it's gonna be a snap!

332
00:22:59,995 --> 00:23:03,226
I'm picturing Sasuke and them
bowing to me and saying,

333
00:23:03,298 --> 00:23:05,926
"Naruto, we're really no match for you."

334
00:23:06,235 --> 00:23:08,931
Huh? Is this for real?!

335
00:23:09,938 --> 00:23:13,931
Next episode: "Start Your Engines:
The Chunin Exam Begins!"

336
00:23:14,009 --> 00:23:16,671
As for me,
I'm going to kick butt once again!
